| `ashishpatel26/500-AI-Agents-Projects` | inspiration catalog | many industry examples and use-case taxonomy |
| `mergisi/awesome-openclaw-agents` | inspiration catalog / template catalog | multi-industry agent templates |
| `VoltAgent/awesome-agent-skills` | skill directory | broad skill discovery and category grouping |
| `agentskills/agentskills` | skill specification | portable skill package format |
| `anthropics/skills` | official skill examples | SKILL.md structure and progressive disclosure |

## Domain Packs

| Repo | Domain | Study for |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `K-Dense-AI/scientific-agent-skills` | science, medicine, research | database-backed scientific and medical workflows |
| `FreedomIntelligence/OpenClaw-Medical-Skills` | medicine | medical skill library structure |
| `aipoch/medical-research-skills` | medical research | protocol, evidence, academic-writing workflow splits |
| `Aperivue/medsci-skills` | medical publishing | skill-suite organization for manuscript workflows |
| `Aperivue/verify-refs` | medical manuscript review | narrow audit-only citation verification |
| `Aperivue/check-reporting` | reporting compliance | checklist status labels and guideline audits |
| `ajhcs/healthcare-agents` | healthcare administration | admin workflow decomposition and role specialists |
| `NVIDIA/digital-health-skills` | digital health | healthcare AI evaluation and metric-driven workflows |
| `awslabs/hcls-agent-skills` | healthcare/life sciences | regulated HCLS skill packaging |
| `ahacker-1/cre-agent-skills` | commercial real estate | underwriting, due diligence, financing, brokerage, closing |
| `jivoi/awesome-osint` | public evidence/source taxonomy | OSINT, public records, geospatial/source discovery |
| `zoharbabin/due-diligence-agents` | M&A/due diligence | cited multi-agent professional review |
| `gs-ai/SYNINT` | OSINT/intelligence | evidence registry, chain of custody, forensic reporting |
| `marieai/marie-ai` | document processing | OCR, extraction, classification, form/document pipelines |
| `microsoft/content-processing-solution-accelerator` | document processing | extraction, schemas, confidence, human review |
| `enescingoz/awesome-n8n-templates` | automation templates | real-world workflow examples; not Codex-native |
| `ritik-prog/n8n-automation-templates-5000` | automation templates | large template corpus; not Codex-native |

## Fit Labels

- `Codex-native`: directly usable as or close to Codex skill/config package.
- `skill/package reference`: useful package structure or reusable skill library.
- `inspiration catalog`: good taxonomy/examples, but not directly installable.
- `runtime/platform`: can execute workflows, but should not replace ECC/Codex
  unless the user explicitly wants that runtime.
- `source taxonomy`: good source list for evidence workflows, not a workflow
  package by itself.

## Known Guidance

- If the user asks for "one repo that combines everything," show the closest
  multi-industry catalogs and explain tradeoffs.
- If the user asks for "popular," include current stars only after live
  verification.
- If the user is building Codex config packages, recommend Codex-compatible
  skills and skill catalogs first. Treat app platforms and UI automators as
  inspiration or optional adapters.
- Do not force a single exact match when the ecosystem is fragmented. Recommend
  a stack of references when that is more honest.


